The Empire of Sentient Man cannot reclaim constant victories over space elves who constantly terrorize human realms. But this doesn’t mean they cannot beat the foe in local skirmishes. The local victories provided to imperials limited weapon exhibits to examine. Besides many elven hover vehicles with controversial fusion of organic and greebled shaped apparatus, defenders of man had found many weapons considered by logics of military art. Some hover tank platoons are followed by self-propelled anti-aircraft engines based on the same platform. They got different names, but the Red Militia called them Zeus. The alternate name was provided due to role similar to small multilaser flak cannons the militia operate.

This model is a turret required for building self-propelled anti-aircraft based on Tiny Space Elves - Beam Hover Tank by Lord_Chronos (https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/tiny-space-elves-beam-hover-tank)

UPDATE 2023.12.14:
- new pin on the turret bottom to fit Beam Hover Tank by Lord_Chronos.

NOTICE:
This model is test printed using Chitubox software, so be careful.

Aetherhawk is a space elven school of crafty Caestopaeifs, infamous for their extremes. Their master architect looked at the needs of world’s Warhost and decided to craft small scale war machines, intended to support smaller warrior squads. He succeeded in providing hover tanks for pathfinding warriors, unaware of the flaws that might bring Warhost in peril. The artisans of friendly Ymbloc world were dissatisfied by greebly looks of apparatus that is supposed to bring energy support to hover vehicles. They stated, the creations of Aetherhawk are a deviation of elven vital designs.

This model is a hull required for building alternate Tiny Space Elves - Transport Hover Tankby Lord_Chronos (https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/tiny-space-elves-transport-hover-tank)

I've never been keen on the current model for this. The older resin version was better, but better still was the late 90s version by Tim Adcock. I've tried to recreate that version but using modern Space Elf designs.

The bulk of the model is Lord Cronos's beam hover tank from here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/tiny-space-elves-beam-hover-tank
With the hover tank turret from here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/tiny-space-elves-hover-tank
The fins at the back of the hull are based on the ones from this model:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/sprue-eldar-hornet
The dispensers are taken from here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/space-elf-support-quasi-classic-platform-weapons

The model is the same scale as Lord Chronos's model on which it is based. For a more traditional 6mm scale, print it scaled to 80%.

The holes in the dispenser will probably need drilling out slightly to fit onto the mounting on the turret. The models all ought to fit but in practice I found that they don't. Alternatively try merging the web spinners with the turret and printing it as one piece.

Here and there the model is quite fragile, so take care when removing supports, assembling the parts or just handling the model.
